      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_fw_info_1a67007fc2be130666fbf3b065022756f4" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int parse</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>parse</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Function to parse the OTA update topic JSON and extract the data. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para>0 in case of succeeds, -1 otherwise</para>
</simplesect>
The function parses the JSON string input by calling function cJSON_Parse provided by the cJSON API and store it in local variable root_obj of type struct cJSON. If parsing failed the function returns immediately with error code -1. Otherwise the objects url_obj, sha1_obj, fw_version_obj, size_obj of type struct cJSON will be extracted from root object root_obj by calling function cJSON_GetObjectItemCaseSensitive with the arguments &quot;url&quot;, &quot;sha1&quot;, &quot;fw_version&quot; and &quot;size&quot;. The resulting object value string will be stored in the private member string variables url, sha1, fw_version and filesize before deleting the root object by call of function cJSON_Delete. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
