      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_fw_info_1a4659b23c49e8463e85dd9c14f9ef5e23" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void splitUrl</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>splitUrl</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Function to split an URL into host and filename. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>The function splits an URL into host and filename. For example: &quot;http://gomera3.ddns.net/stg/app_update.bin&quot; will be split into<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>host: gomera3.ddns.net</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>filename: /stg/app_update.bin The function copy the url into a local string tmp, search for protocol part in url, store it in member variable proto and delete it from string tmp. Than it extract host string and store it in member variable host and delete it also from string tmp. Finally the remaining filename part will be stored in member variable filename. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
